Title : Tarlok Singh (athlete)
Text : {{BLP sources|date = January 2015}}'''Tarlok Singh''' was an [[India]]n long-distance runner who won a gold medal in the 10000&nbsp;meters and a bronze medal in the 5000&nbsp;meters runs in the 1962 Jakarta Asian Games.<ref>{{cite web |title=Asian Games |url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/ic/asg.htm |accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> Subsequently, he was affected by [[tuberculosis]] because of malnutrition and succumbed to it without nearly receiving any medical treatment.

